100
00:07:14,517 --> 00:07:16,816
So he couldn't refuse and took the job on reluctantly.

101
00:07:16,817 --> 00:07:19,716
Even so, if the residents pushes him to do something,

102
00:07:19,717 --> 00:07:22,016
he couldn't have avoided talking to Mr. Amagi...

103
00:07:22,017 --> 00:07:24,316
Of course.

104
00:07:24,317 --> 00:07:27,217
We're all paying community fees after all, you know.

105
00:07:28,217 --> 00:07:33,616
Apparently that woman, Ms. Hiro Ezaki, was pestering him the most.

106
00:07:33,617 --> 00:07:35,516
She does look like a strong woman.

107
00:07:35,517 --> 00:07:37,516
It seems that he was not all that dependent,

108
00:07:37,517 --> 00:07:40,916
so he carried that awl to protect himself.

109
00:07:40,917 --> 00:07:44,616
What do you want, asking me to come to a place like this?

110
00:07:44,617 --> 00:07:45,716
That...

111
00:07:45,717 --> 00:07:47,016
What?

112
00:07:47,017 --> 00:07:48,816
Come on, say it!

113
00:07:48,817 --> 00:07:51,416
Just what do you want?

114
00:07:51,417 --> 00:07:54,116
So, Mr. Bando who panicked,

115
00:07:54,117 --> 00:07:56,017
probably in advertently...

116
00:08:06,717 --> 00:08:10,817
But since Mr. Bando figured he couldn't get away with it...

117
00:08:12,117 --> 00:08:14,216
Gave up and committed suicide.

118
00:08:14,217 --> 00:08:17,617
I guess you could say this is a bitter type of case closed.

119
00:08:18,317 --> 00:08:20,517
Don't rush to conclusions.

120
00:08:21,517 --> 00:08:24,516
Well, then I guess everything worked out right.

121
00:08:24,517 --> 00:08:26,616
That unreliable useless guy

122
00:08:26,617 --> 00:08:30,316
finally was of some use to the community.

123
00:08:30,317 --> 00:08:33,616
To stab a nuisance who was hated by everyone,

124
00:08:33,617 --> 00:08:36,017
how convenient can things get.

125
00:08:39,517 --> 00:08:43,616
But I don't think so.

126
00:08:43,617 --> 00:08:47,916
Mr. Bando would never be able to cause such an incident.

127
00:08:47,917 --> 00:08:49,216
Really?

128
00:08:49,217 --> 00:08:51,416
If it wasn't inadvertently...

129
00:08:51,417 --> 00:08:54,016
To begin, Mr. Bando was not all that concerned

130
00:08:54,017 --> 00:08:56,516
about Mr. Amagi being a problem.

131
00:08:56,517 --> 00:08:59,416
Even yesterday, he was laughing about it.

132
00:08:59,417 --> 00:09:01,816
I'd like you to give me more in detail.

133
00:09:01,817 --> 00:09:03,016
You are...

134
00:09:03,017 --> 00:09:05,516
I'm Toyoko Kanemitsu.

135
00:09:05,517 --> 00:09:09,116
Oh, you can't cross that line.

136
00:09:09,117 --> 00:09:13,316
Then why don't we go to my place to talk?

137
00:09:13,317 --> 00:09:15,916
No, we don't need to go out of our way to move places.

138
00:09:15,917 --> 00:09:17,016
Right.

139
00:09:17,017 --> 00:09:20,516
Oh my god, you're the famed Detective Mouri, aren't you?

140
00:09:20,517 --> 00:09:22,016
Please do come over too, Mr. Mouri.

141
00:09:22,017 --> 00:09:25,016
I run a small coffee right nearby.

142
00:09:25,017 --> 00:09:26,916
Really?

143
00:09:26,917 --> 00:09:28,016
Okay, then.

144
00:09:28,017 --> 00:09:29,317
Hey...

145
00:09:38,617 --> 00:09:40,816
Here you are.

146
00:09:40,817 --> 00:09:42,517
Thank you.

147
00:09:46,917 --> 00:09:48,116
Here you go.

148
00:09:48,117 --> 00:09:49,716
Thank you.

149
00:09:49,717 --> 00:09:52,616
When did Mr. Bando came yesterday?

150
00:09:52,617 --> 00:09:54,016
"Koyuki Gamo (23), Waitress" -Oh...

151
00:09:54,017 --> 00:09:56,716
I think it was a little past noon.

152
00:09:56,717 --> 00:09:57,916
That's right.

153
00:09:57,917 --> 00:10:01,716
He was together with his friend Mr. Yosuke Chino,

154
00:10:01,717 --> 00:10:04,917
who teaches Japanese History at Haido University.

